{"questionId":"9076191","questionHtml":"<p>The student plots a graph to show how <em>P</em><sup>2</sup> varies with <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\frac{1}{B}\">\n  <mfrac>\n    <mn>1</mn>\n    <mi>B</mi>\n  </mfrac>\n</math></span>&nbsp;for the data.</p>\n<p>Sketch the shape of the expected line of best fit on the axes below assuming that the relationship <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"P = \\frac{K}{{\\sqrt B }}\">\n  <mi>P</mi>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mfrac>\n    <mi>K</mi>\n    <mrow>\n      <msqrt>\n        <mi>B</mi>\n      </msqrt>\n    </mrow>\n  </mfrac>\n</math></span>&nbsp;is verified. You do <strong>not </strong>have to put numbers on the axes.</p>\n<p><img src=\"__IMG__/950fb9bce19484107ee9d8f7f663e55c03cd98a3.png\"></p>","markschemeHtml":"<p>straight <strong><em>AND </em></strong>ascending line</p>\n<p>through origin</p>\n<p><em><strong>[2 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"9076191","referenceCode":"18M.3.SL.TZ1.1c","subjectId":"46-dp-physics-last-assessment-2024","title":"The student plots a graph to show how P2 varies with 1 B for the data. Sketch the shape of the expected line of best fit on the axes below assuming that the relationship P = K B is","paper":"3","level":"SL","questionNumber":"c","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Core","Core","Topic 1: Measurements and uncertainties","1.2 – Uncertainties and errors","Core","Topic 1: Measurements and uncertainties"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}}}